Usage: mpk [options] [path to file or directory]

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit

  Actions:
    -i, --info          Show info
    -n, --rename        Rename files to standard names
    -C, --copy          Copy into repository
    -e, --extract       Extract streams for processing
    -T, --tag           Update file tags
    -O, --optimize      Optimize file layout
    -t KIND, --transcode=KIND
                        KIND is one of [m4v, mkv, srt, txt, jpg, png, ac3]
    -c KIND, --transform=KIND
                        KIND is one of [m4v]
    -P KIND, --pack=KIND
                        KIND is one of [mkv, m4v]
    -u KIND, --update=KIND
                        KIND is one of [srt, png, jpg, txt, m4v]

  Action modifiers:
    -o VOLUME, --volume=VOLUME
    -p PROFILE, --profile=PROFILE
    -q QUANTIZER, --quality=QUANTIZER
    -r, --recursive     Recursively process sub directories
    -w, --overwrite     Overwrite existing files
    -W WIDTH, --width=WIDTH
                        Override profile output pixel width
    -f REGEX, --filter=REGEX
                        File name regex filter

  Subtitles:
    --NTSC              Convert PAL to NTSC framerate
    --PAL               Convert NTSC to PAL framerate
    --shift=TIME        Shift offset in millisec
    --input-rate=RATE   Subtitles decoding frame rate
    --output-rate=RATE  Subtitles encoding frame rate

  Environment:
    -S, --sync          Sync encountered records with online service
    -U, --reindex       Rebuild physical file index
    -D, --download      Download if local is unavailable
    -M MAP, --map-show=MAP
                        Map show to tvdb id [tvdb id]:[show name]
    --choose-movie-poster=MAP
                        Choose tmdb movie poster [imdb]:[tmdb]
    -l CODE, --language=CODE
                        Languge code to use when und [default: eng]
    --initialize        Run only once to initialize the system
    -5, --md5           Verify md5 checksum after copy
    -d, --debug         Only print commands without executing
    -v LEVEL, --verbosity=LEVEL
                        Logging verbosity level [default: info]
